ing with class literals that follow the public API requiring class inputs. I wonder if there’s a need to avoid creating inner classes. It appears that a test class file should correlate directly without reports, and inner static classes don’t match top-level classes.\"},{\"type\":\"summary_text\",\"text\":\"**Exploring JUnit testing considerations**\\n\\nI’m thinking names and files have different rules, which is interesting. Maybe the Spock JUnit runner reflects nested classes, so I want a comprehensive approach with a metadata generator capturing everything. It seems important to ensure that only top-level public classes are considered.\\n\\nI could avoid using an exact runCount for unrolls since it might introduce confusion. I can assert at least one run, which could be meaningful. For lifecycles, external static ensures both features, and data results should be fairly static. \\n\\nI also need some imports, particularly for JUnit classes, and I’m curious about potential compilation issues with AssertJ in Groovy.\"},{\"type\":\"summary_text\",\"text\":\"**Considering class visibility in Groovy**\\n\\nI'm pondering a potential compile issue with static nested specs in a package-private context. It seems I should make sure they're declared as public static classes. In Groovy, I think nested classes default to public, but top-level classes also default to public unless specified otherwise. I need to use annotations like `@Stepwise` and `@Title` in the Spock specification, so I'll ensure to include those imports. It's time to write out the code with these considerations!\"}]}"}, {"type": "toolCall", "id": "call_U9trO4UjZ1gwzU9zU3IdqgFz|fc_03e86946db7ddd75016a270738fbcc81949ada0f0aecc8a321", "name": "write", "arguments": {"path": "tests/src/org.spockframework/spock-core/1.0-groovy-2.4/src/test/groovy/org_spockframework/spock_core/Spock_coreTest.groovy", "content": "/*\n * Copyright and related rights waived via CC0\n *\n * You should have received a copy of the CC0 legalcode along with this\n * work. If not, see <http://creativecommons.org/publicdomain/zero/1.0/>.\n */\npackage org_spockframework.spock_core\n\nimport org.junit.jupiter.api.Test\nimport org.junit.runner.JUnitCore\nimport org.junit.runner.Result\nimport org.junit.runner.notification.Failure\nimport spock.lang.Narrative\nimport spock.lang.Specification\nimport spock.lang.Stepwise\nimport spock.lang.Title\nimport spock.lang.Unroll\n\nimport static org.assertj.core.api.Assertions.assertThat\n\npublic class Spock_coreTest {\n    @Test\n    void runsFixtureLifecycleAndDataDrivenSpecifications() {\n        FixtureLifecycleSpec.resetEvents()\n        DataDrivenSpec.resetObservedResults()\n\n        Result result = JUnitCore.runClasses(FixtureLifecycleSpec, DataDrivenSpec)\n\n        assertSuccessful(result)\n        assertThat(FixtureLifecycleSpec.events).containsExactly(\n                'setupSpec',\n                'setup', 'first feature', 'cleanup',\n                'setup', 'second feature', 'cleanup',\n                'cleanupSpec')\n        assertThat(DataDrivenSpec.observedResults).containsExactly(\n                '1 + 2 = 3',\n                '2 + 3 = 5',\n                '3 + 5 = 8')\n    }\n\n    @Test\n    void runsInteractionBasedMockingAndStubbingSpecifications() {\n        Result result = JUnitCore.runClasses(InteractionSpec, StubbedCollaboratorSpec)\n\n        assertSuccessful(result)\n    }\n\n    @Test\n    void runsExceptionAndConditionSpecifications() {\n        Result result = JUnitCore.runClasses(ExceptionConditionSpec, CollectionConditionSpec)\n\n        assertSuccessful(result)\n    }\n\n    private static void assertSuccessful(Result result) {\n        List<String> failures = result.failures.collect { Failure failure ->\n            \"${failure.testHeader}: ${failure.message}\".toString()\n        }\n        assertThat(failures).isEmpty()\n        assertThat(result.wasSuccessful()).isTrue()\n    }\n\n    @Stepwise\n    @Title('Fixture lifecycle specification')\n    @Narrative('Exercises setupSpec, setup, cleanup, cleanupSpec, and feature execution ordering.')\n    public static class FixtureLifecycleSpec extends Specification {\n        static List<String> events = []\n\n        static void resetEvents() {\n            events.clear()\n        }\n\n        def setupSpec() {\n            events << 'setupSpec'\n        }\n\n        def setup() {\n            events << 'setup'\n        }\n\n        def cleanup() {\n            events << 'cleanup'\n        }\n\n        def cleanupSpec() {\n            events << 'cleanupSpec'\n        }\n\n        def 'first feature records its body'() {\n            expect:\n            events << 'first feature'\n        }\n\n        def 'second feature records its body'() {\n            expect:\n            events << 'second feature'\n        }\n    }\n\n    public static class DataDrivenSpec extends Specification {\n        static List<String> observedResults = []\n\n        static void resetObservedResults() {\n            observedResults.clear()\n        }\n\n        @Unroll\n        def 'adds #left and #right to make #sum'() {\n            expect:\n            left + right == sum\n\n            cleanup:\n            observedResults << \"${left} + ${right} = ${sum}\".toString()\n\n            where:\n            left | right || sum\n            1    | 2     || 3\n            2    | 3     || 5\n            3    | 5     || 8\n        }\n    }\n\n    public static class InteractionSpec extends Specification {\n        def 'mock verifies interaction counts, argument constraints, and responses'() {\n            given:\n            GreetingService greetingService = Mock()\n\n            when:\n            String message = greetingService.greet('Ada')\n            greetingService.recordVisit('Grace')\n\n            then:\n            1 * greetingService.greet('Ada') >> 'Hello Ada'\n            1 * greetingService.recordVisit({ String name -> name.startsWith('Gra') })\n            0 * _\n            message == 'Hello Ada'\n        }\n    }\n\n    public static class StubbedCollaboratorSpec extends Specification {\n        def 'stub supplies deterministic values to production style collaborator code'() {\n            given:\n            PriceCatalog catalog = Stub()\n            catalog.priceOf('book') >> 12G\n            catalog.priceOf('pen') >> 3G\n            Checkout checkout = new Checkout(catalog)\n\n            expect:\n            checkout.total(['book', 'pen', 'pen']) == 18G\n        }\n    }\n\n    public static class ExceptionConditionSpec extends Specification {\n        def 'thrown captures exception type and message'() {\n            when:\n            parsePositiveInteger('-7')\n\n            then:\n            IllegalArgumentException exception = thrown()\n            exception.message == 'value must be positive: -7'\n        }\n\n        def 'notThrown confirms valid input path'() {\n            when:\n            Integer value = parsePositiveInteger('21')\n\n            then:\n            notThrown(IllegalArgumentException)\n            value == 21\n        }\n\n        private static Integer parsePositiveInteger(String value) {\n            Integer parsed = Integer.valueOf(value)\n            if (parsed <= 0) {\n                throw new IllegalArgumentException(\"value must be positive: ${value}\".toString())\n            }\n            return parsed\n        }\n    }\n\n    public static class CollectionConditionSpec extends Specification {\n        def 'conditions support Groovy collection operations in feature methods'() {\n            given:\n            List<String> names = ['ada', 'grace', 'alan']\n\n            expect:\n            names.findAll { String name -> name.contains('a') }\n                    .collect { String name -> name.capitalize() } == ['Ada', 'Grace', 'Alan']\n            names.groupBy { String name -> name.length() }[5] == ['grace']\n        }\n    }\n\n    static interface GreetingService {\n        String greet(String name)\n\n        void recordVisit(String name)\n    }\n\n    static interface PriceCatalog {\n        BigDecimal priceOf(String item)\n    }\n\n    static class Checkout {\n        private final PriceCatalog catalog\n\n        Checkout(PriceCatalog catalog) {\n            this.catalog = catalog\n        }\n\n        BigDecimal total(List<String> items) {\n            return items.collect { String item -> catalog.priceOf(item) }.sum() as BigDecimal\n        }\n    }\n}\n"}}], "api": "openai-responses", "provider": "OCA", "model": "oca/gpt-5.5", "usage": {"input": 2383, "output": 1980, "cacheRead": 16896, "cacheWrite": 0, "totalTokens": 21259, "cost": {"input": 0, "output": 0, "cacheRead": 0, "cacheWrite": 0, "total": 0}}, "stopReason": "toolUse", "timestamp": 1780942635070, "responseId": "resp_03e86946db7ddd75016a27072b6cf4819494265ea76b5754a5"}, "toolResults": [{"role": "toolResult", "toolCallId": "call_U9trO4UjZ1gwzU9zU3IdqgFz|fc_03e86946db7ddd75016a270738fbcc81949ada0f0aecc8a321", "toolName": "write", "content": [{"type": "text", "text": "Successfully wrote 6381 bytes to tests/src/org.spockframework/spock-core/1.0-groovy-2.4/src/test/groovy/org_spockframework/spock_core/Spock_coreTest.groovy"}], "isError": false, "timestamp": 1780942667029}]}
